      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Anomaly Scoring with Soft Assignments"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Because GMM provides a full density model, log p(x) is a principled anomaly score — points in low-density regions get low scores regardless of which component is closest."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "codeBlock",
        "attrs": {
          "language": "python"
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "# Anomaly detection: flag points below the 1st percentile of log p(x)\nlog_px = gmm.score_samples(X)          # (N,)  — log p(xₙ)\nthreshold = np.percentile(log_px, 1)\nanomalies = X[log_px < threshold]\nprint(f\"Anomaly threshold: log p(x) < {threshold:.2f}\")\nprint(f\"Found {len(anomalies)} anomalies out of {len(X)} points\")\n\n# The soft-assignment entropy is complementary:\n# a point near a component boundary may have HIGH entropy\n# but still be a normal point with moderate p(x).\n# A true outlier has LOW p(x) AND low responsibility under all components."
          }
        ]
      }
